reviews.review:
'Portal 2' may just be the most enjoyable single-player game I have ever played - and I will provide you with five reasons why!

- Firstly, the dialogue is brilliant;
- The story is surprisingly engaging, and your 'companion', Wheatley, is highly entertaining, although perhaps a little too talkative for some; 
- The atmosphere is highly immersive, with a variety of settings ranging from - without spoiling too much - underground to laboratories to factories;
- Very rewarding puzzles that challenge you without becoming monotonous or frustrating. This is entirely subjective, though, so some of you may dissent from this view; and
- The co-op mode provides more content to enjoy with a friend. Truth be told, I found this mode to be more enjoyable than the single-player! And to that end, the prospect of replaying the co-op mode is certainly appealing IF you are fortunate enough to a) have more than 1 friend who owns the game, and b) own more than one friend. 

11/10 GET THE GAME!
